Low-Dose Intravenous Immunoglobulin Treatment for Long-Standing Complex Regional 
Pain Syndrome: A Randomized Trial.

Goebel A(1), Bisla J(1), Carganillo R(1), Frank B(1), Gupta R(1), Kelly J(1), 
McCabe C(1), Murphy C(1), Padfield N(1), Phillips C(1), Sanders M(1), Serpell 
M(1), Shenker N(1), Shoukrey K(1), Wyatt L(1), Ambler G(1).

Author information:
(1)From University of Liverpool and The Walton Centre National Health Service 
(NHS) Foundation Trust, Liverpool; Institute of Psychiatry, Psychology and 
Neuroscience, Guy's and St Thomas' Hospital, and University College London, 
London; Modepharma Limited, Beckenham; Queen Elizabeth University Hospital, 
Glasgow; University West of England, Bristol; Swansea University, Swansea; 
Norfolk and Norwich University NHS Trust, Norwich; Cambridge University 
Hospitals, Cambridge; and University Hospitals of Leicester NHS Trust, 
